The chemotherapy of most cancers may be beneficial to older individuals as long 
as patients are selected on the basis of their life expectancy and functional 
reserve, conditions that may interfere with the tolerance of chemotherapy are 
corrected, and adequate doses of chemotherapy are administered. Prevention of 
neutropenia-related infection may both improve the outcome of cancer and reduce 
