As a component of the response to acute stress, p53 has a well established role 
in protecting against cancer development. However, it is now becoming clear that 
p53 can have a much broader role and can contribute to the development, life 
expectancy and overall fitness of an organism. Although the function of p53 as a 
tumour suppressor ensures that we can't live without it, an integrated view of 
p53 suggests that not all of its functions are conducive to a long and healthy 
life.

